<br>
1.  Work with the EQ Hawks well!<br>
2.  Deligate responsibility broadly.  The Hawks are great because of each and every member.  <br>
3.  Make good use of the new toys and flexibility to create more opportunities and specific roles within the guild.<br>
<br>
It's important to note that Officers in DAoC serve a little different role then that of EQ.  Officers as we knew them in EQ are considered Nobles (executive officers) in DAoC, Exec Officers in EQ will now be the Magistrate (#2) and Noble Treasurer, and outstanding members that are inclined, will be our Earls.  We should have 1 Earl for every 3 or 4 members.  <br>
<br>
For our esteemed members who do not want the responsibility of officership, the rank of Elder is reserved for you.  It fits above our Earls, but below our Nobles.  If you are an Elder, you also have access to Alliance chat.<br>
<br>
Inviting someone into the initiate role should be a common practice when Earls meet likeable people that are even remotely interested in joining our guild.  Once someone has had a chance to experience SH guild chat, visit our message board and website, sign up for our roster and policies, we will then promote them into the guild with honor.  This may even involve a ceremony.<br>
<br>
I hope that this new system allows for growth while maintaining a sense of pride and honor that we've always experienced together as a guild. <br>
 <br>
0 <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>           Patriarch</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->The game doesn't allow me to remove access from any of the features... even if I wanted to.<br>
<br>
1 <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>           Magistrate</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> The #2. All features enabled. Acting leader in the Patriarch's absence.<br>
<br>
2 <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>           Noble Treasurer</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Same as a Noble, yet has access to withdraw from the treasury. Anyone is allowed to deposit, but only the leader, magistrate, and treasurer have the access to make an withdrawal.<br>
<br>
3 <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>           Noble</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Our executive officers. Same as the Treasurer except the Noble is unable to withdraw from the treasurary.  Nobles can also promote members up to the rank of Elder and remove a member if required.<br>
<br>
4 <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>           Elder</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Essentially the same as our members, but ranked with the officer. This is a title reserved for our older and esteemed members who do not desire the responsibilities that the Elder and Noble posts require. <br>
<br>
5 <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>           Earl</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Ability to invite, but unable to remove. Access to officer chat as well. Our earls should be the backbone to our guild. It will not be terribly difficult to become an officer, but it is an honored position and one that is expected to be served by our outstanding members. I'm thinking that an ideal ratio of officers to members should be around 1/4 or even 1/3. This post is also going to be an integral part of our siege and defence efforts on the battle field as they are the final line of communication between the nobles and leader and the guild.  Earls can promote initiates to full members.<br>
<br>
6 <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>           Silver Hawk</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Esteemed members of our fine guild. Members can view the guild info and wear emblems.  Silver Hawk members also have access to our alliance chat.  <br>
<br>
9 <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>           Initiate</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> This is the rank that everyone is automatically given when they are first invited. Initiates will be able to participate in our guild chat, but will not be able to view the guild info or wear an emblem until promoted to Silver Hawk or higher.<br>
<br>
7 <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>           Guest</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> This is something that we could use some day or not... I know it would have been handy in EQ. Unguilded people who join our guild meetings etc. could be invited and be a Guest. Also nice for raiding and even extended hunts because it's safe as this rank has access to our guild chat only. <p><html>
